{
  "texts": [
    "This baseline establishes that the tested models are trained to disclose AI identities by default system prompts.However, models assigned professional personas demonstrate widespread failures in disclosing AI identities.",
    "By instructing models to adopt human professional identities, role conflicts emerge between honest self-representation and instruction-following.Table 1 shows disclosure rates averaged across all models and prompts for each persona.",
    "While baseline personas maintained near-perfect disclosure, professional personas reduced disclosure universally in the sample.",
    "Averaged across all models and prompts, disclosure ranged from 24.4% to 61.0% across professional personas.Figure 2 reveals substantial model heterogeneity within this universal suppression effect.",
    "Performance variation spans a 26-fold range."
  ]
}